HOUSE BILL 1411
M5, L6, Q4 6lr3562
By: Delegate Ruth
Introduced and read first time: February 13, 2026
Assigned to: Environment and Transportation
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Data Center Planning and Transparency Act
3 FOR the purpose of requiring an owner or operator of a certain large–scale data center to
4 submit a certain disclosure report to certain State and local agencies and elected
5 officials under certain circumstances; specifying the contents of the disclosure report;
6 requiring the Department of the Environment to publish the disclosure report on its
7 website within a certain period of time; requiring, on or before a certain date, each
8 local jurisdiction with a certain population of residents to develop and adopt by local
9 law a large–scale data center plan in a certain manner; requiring certain local
10 jurisdictions to submit the plan to the Department of Planning within a certain
11 period of time; requiring the Department of Planning to publish the plan on its
12 website within a certain period of time; requiring certain local jurisdictions to adopt
13 zoning regulations to implement the plan; prohibiting an officer or a unit of State
14 government from using any part of an appropriation to provide certain financial
15 assistance or incentives to an owner or operator of a large–scale data center unless
16 certain conditions are met; altering the requirements for qualified data center
17 personal property to be eligible for an exemption from the sales and use tax; and
18 generally relating to data centers.
19 BY adding to
20 Article – Environment
21 Section 19–101 and 19–102 to be under the new title “Title 19. Data Centers”
22 Annotated Code of Maryland
23 (2014 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
24 BY adding to
25 Article – Land Use
26 Section 1–401(b)(19) and 4–217
27 Annotated Code of Maryland
28 (2012 Volume and 2025 Supplement)
