21 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
22 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
23 Article – Environment
24 TITLE 19. DATA CENTERS.
25 19–101.
26 (A) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
27 INDICATED.
28 (B) “DATA CENTER” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 11–239 OF THE TAX –
29 GENERAL ARTICLE.
30 (C) “DISCLOSURE REPORT” MEANS THE DISCLOSURE REPORT THAT AN
31 OWNER OR OPERATOR OF A PROPOSED, PLANNED, OR APPROVED LARGE–SCALE
32 DATA CENTER IS REQUIRED TO PROVIDE UNDER § 19–102 OF THIS TITLE.
33 (D) “LARGE–SCALE DATA CENTER” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN §
34 4–217 OF THE LAND USE ARTICLE.

HOUSE BILL 1411 3
1 (E) “MULTITENANT DATA CENTER” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 4–217
2 OF THE LAND USE ARTICLE.
3 19–102.
4 (A) (1) AN OWNER OR OPERATOR OF A PROPOSED, PLANNED, OR
5 APPROVED LARGE–SCALE DATA CENTER SHALL SUBMIT A DISCLOSURE REPORT TO:
6 (I) THE DEPARTMENT;
7 (II) THE MARYLAND ENERGY ADMINISTRATION;
8 (III) THE LOCAL APPROVING AUTHORITIES FOR PLANNING,
9 ECONOMIC DEVELOPMENT, PERMITTING, AND ENVIRONMENT, AS APPLICABLE, OF
10 THE LOCAL JURISDICTION IN WHICH THE DATA CENTER WILL BE LOCATED; AND
11 (IV) ANY STATE AND LOCAL ELECTED OFFICIAL REPRESENTING
12 THE AREA IN WHICH THE DATA CENTER WILL BE LOCATED.
13 (2) A DISCLOSURE REPORT SHALL BE SUBMITTED TO THE ENTITIES
14 LISTED IN PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION BY THE EARLIER OF THE
15 FOLLOWING:
16 (I) 60 DAYS BEFORE THE OWNER OR OPERATOR SUBMITS AN
17 APPLICATION FOR ANY GRANT, LOAN, OR OTHER FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE OR
18 INCENTIVE, INCLUDING A TAX INCENTIVE, TO A UNIT OF STATE GOVERNMENT; OR
19 (II) 60 DAYS BEFORE THE OWNER OR OPERATOR SUBMITS AN
20 APPLICATION FOR ANY PERMIT, APPROVAL, OR LICENSE REQUIRED BY FEDERAL,
21 STATE, OR LOCAL LAW TO CONSTRUCT OR OPERATE A LARGE–SCALE DATA CENTER.
22 (B) A DISCLOSURE REPORT SHALL INCLUDE:
23 (1) THE NAME AND ADDRESS OF:
24 (I) THE FACILITY;
25 (II) THE OPERATOR OF THE FACILITY; AND
26 (III) THE OWNER OF THE LAND, BUILDING, AND COMPUTER
27 EQUIPMENT ASSOCIATED WITH THE FACILITY;
28 (2) A DETAILED DESCRIPTION FOR:

4 HOUSE BILL 1411
1 (I) DEMONSTRATING THE NEED FOR THE FACILITY;
2 (II) EXPLAINING THE REASONING FOR THE LOCATION OF THE
3 FACILITY; AND
4 (III) OUTLINING THE COMMUNITY BENEFITS THAT WILL BE
5 PROVIDED BY THE FACILITY;
6 (3) INFORMATION ON WHETHER:
7 (I) THE OWNER OR OPERATOR HAS SIGNED AN
8 INTERCONNECTION AGREEMENT, AND IF SO:
9 1. THE STATUS OF THE FACILITY’S INTERCONNECTION
10 TO A UTILITY SYSTEM OR TRANSMISSION GRID; AND
11 2. WHETHER A LOAD STUDY HAS ALREADY BEEN
12 CONDUCTED;
13 (II) THE FACILITY HAS BEEN PREVIOUSLY PROPOSED AT
14 ANOTHER LOCATION IN THE STATE OR IN ANOTHER STATE; AND
15 (III) THE FACILITY IS A MULTITENANT DATA CENTER;
16 (4) THE TOTAL SQUARE FOOTAGE OF THE FACILITY;
17 (5) THE MEAN AMOUNT OF PROJECTED DAILY ELECTRICITY USAGE
18 MEASURED IN MEGAWATTS;
19 (6) THE MEAN AMOUNT OF PROJECTED ELECTRICITY USAGE PER
20 HOUR DURING PEAK LOAD MEASURED IN MEGAWATTS AND FREQUENCY OF PEAK
21 LOAD PER WEEK;
22 (7) THE SOURCE OF POWER FOR THE FACILITY, INCLUDING A COPY
23 OF ANY POWER PURCHASE AGREEMENT FOR SUPPLYING ELECTRICITY TO THE
24 FACILITY WITH AN ESTIMATE ON THE LEVEL OF GREENHOUSE GAS EMISSIONS
25 ASSOCIATED WITH THE PROJECTED ELECTRICITY USAGE;
26 (8) ANY ANTICIPATED NEED FOR ADDITIONAL POWER
27 INFRASTRUCTURE, INCLUDING TRANSMISSION LINES AND SUBSTATIONS;

HOUSE BILL 1411 5
1 (9) THE NUMBER, SIZE, FUEL SOURCE, AND PROJECTED EMISSIONS
2 OF ANY BACKUP GENERATORS FOR THE FACILITY;
3 (10) THE TYPE, CAPACITY, AND PROJECTED EMISSIONS OF ANY
4 ON–SITE GENERATION FOR REGULAR OPERATION;
5 (11) THE TYPE OF COOLING SYSTEM, SOURCES OF WATER, AND
6 ESTIMATED VOLUME OF WATER APPROPRIATION NEEDED, IF APPLICABLE;
7 (12) THE PROJECTED NOISE LEVELS EMITTED BY THE FACILITY
8 ESTIMATED IN DECIBELS:
9 (I) 1. AT THE FACILITY PROPERTY LINE; AND
10 2. AT PROPERTIES LOCATED WITHIN A 0.25–MILE,
11 0.50–MILE, AND 1.0–MILE RADIUS OF THE FACILITY PROPERTY LINE; AND
12 (II) FOR WHEN THE FACILITY WILL BE OPERATING ALL
13 COOLING AND COMPUTER EQUIPMENT AND REGULAR TESTING OF ALL EMERGENCY
14 GENERATORS AT FULL LOAD;
15 (13) ESTIMATED MILESTONE DATES FOR DESIGN AND CONSTRUCTION;
16 (14) THE NUMBER AND TYPE OF PERMANENT POSTCONSTRUCTION
17 JOBS THE FACILITY WILL PROVIDE; AND
18 (15) ANY STATE, COUNTY, OR LOCAL GRANT, LOAN, OR OTHER
19 FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE OR INCENTIVE, INCLUDING A TAX INCENTIVE, THE OWNER
20 OR OPERATOR OF THE FACILITY INTENDS TO APPLY FOR.
21 (C) IF THERE ARE SUBSTANTIAL CHANGES TO ANY OF THE ITEMS REQUIRED
22 UNDER SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION, THE OWNER OR OPERATOR OF THE
23 LARGE–SCALE DATA CENTER SHALL SUBMIT AN AMENDED DISCLOSURE REPORT IN
24 ACCORDANCE WITH THIS SECTION.
25 (D) (1) NEITHER THE DISCLOSURE REPORT NOR ANY OF ITS CONTENTS
26 SHALL BE CONSIDERED PRIVILEGED OR CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION.
27 (2) WITHIN 30 DAYS AFTER RECEIVING A DISCLOSURE REPORT, THE
28 DEPARTMENT SHALL PUBLISH THE DISCLOSURE REPORT ON ITS WEBSITE.
