23 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
24 INDICATED.

HOUSE BILL 1411 7
1 (2) “DATA CENTER” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 11–239 OF THE
2 TAX – GENERAL ARTICLE.
3 (3) (I) “LARGE–SCALE DATA CENTER” MEANS A DATA CENTER
4 THAT IS PROJECTED TO HAVE AN AGGREGATE MONTHLY DEMAND OF AT LEAST 20
5 MEGAWATTS.
6 (II) “LARGE–SCALE DATA CENTER” INCLUDES A MULTITENANT
7 DATA CENTER THAT IS PROJECTED TO HAVE AN AGGREGATE MONTHLY DEMAND OF
8 AT LEAST 20 MEGAWATTS.
9 (4) “MULTITENANT DATA CENTER” MEANS A FACILITY THAT LEASES
10 SPACE TO MULTIPLE DATA CENTER OPERATORS AND MAY PROVIDE SHARED
11 SERVICES INCLUDING POWER, COOLING, AND INTERNET CONNECTIVITY.
12 (5) “PLAN” MEANS THE LARGE–SCALE DATA CENTER PLAN ADOPTED
13 BY A LOCAL JURISDICTION UNDER THIS SECTION.
14 (B) THIS SECTION APPLIES ONLY TO A LOCAL JURISDICTION WITH A
15 POPULATION OF AT LEAST 10,000 RESIDENTS.
16 (C) (1) ON OR BEFORE JUNE 30, 2027, EACH LOCAL JURISDICTION SHALL
17 DEVELOP AND ADOPT BY LOCAL LAW A LARGE–SCALE DATA CENTER PLAN IN
18 ACCORDANCE WITH THIS SECTION.
19 (2) WITHIN 60 DAYS AFTER ADOPTING THE PLAN, THE LOCAL
20 JURISDICTION SHALL SUBMIT THE PLAN TO THE DEPARTMENT OF PLANNING.
21 (D) THE PLAN SHALL:
22 (1) BE CONSISTENT WITH THE LOCAL JURISDICTION’S SUSTAINABLE
23 GROWTH PRINCIPLES AND COMPREHENSIVE PLAN;
24 (2) INCLUDE POLICIES THAT:
25 (I) PROMOTE SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT AND PROTECT THE
26 ENVIRONMENT;
27 (II) MAINTAIN COMMUNITY CHARACTER;
28 (III) ENSURE A TRANSPARENT AND INCLUSIVE PROCESS;
29 (IV) MAXIMIZE LOCAL ECONOMIC BENEFITS;

8 HOUSE BILL 1411
1 (V) PROTECT COMMUNITY AND PUBLIC HEALTH; AND
2 (VI) PROTECT UTILITY RATEPAYERS; AND
3 (3) INCLUDE RECOMMENDATIONS FOR:
4 (I) SITING GUIDELINES, INCLUDING LOCATIONS WHERE
5 LARGE–SCALE DATA CENTER DEVELOPMENT MAY BE DESIRABLE AND LOCATIONS
6 WHERE DEVELOPMENT SHOULD BE RESTRICTED, WITH CONSIDERATION FOR:
7 1. UNDERSERVED AND OVERBURDENED COMMUNITIES;
8 2. AREAS CERTIFIED AS A PRIORITY PRESERVATION
9 AREA UNDER § 2–518 OF THE AGRICULTURE ARTICLE;
10 3. AREAS DESIGNATED BY THE RURAL LEGACY BOARD
11 AS A RURAL LEGACY AREA UNDER TITLE 5, SUBTITLE 9A OF THE NATURAL
12 RESOURCES ARTICLE;
13 4. AGRICULTURAL LAND;
14 5. UNDEVELOPED LAND; AND
15 6. PROXIMITY TO SCHOOLS, DAYCARES, PARKS, OR
16 MEDICAL FACILITIES;
17 (II) ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION, WITH CONSIDERATION FOR
18 CUMULATIVE IMPACTS;
19 (III) REQUIREMENTS FOR PUBLIC NOTICE THAT PROVIDE AN
20 OPPORTUNITY FOR PUBLIC INPUT MEETINGS AND ENSURE ONGOING PROJECT
21 TRANSPARENCY, INCLUDING REQUIRING AT LEAST TWO PUBLIC INPUT MEETINGS
22 BEFORE ANY LOCAL DEVELOPMENT PLANS OR PERMITS FOR A LARGE–SCALE DATA
23 CENTER ARE APPROVED;
24 (IV) REQUIREMENTS FOR COMMUNITY BENEFITS;
25 (V) CONSIDERATIONS FOR LOCATING ADDITIONAL POWER
26 SUPPORT INFRASTRUCTURE THAT MAY BE NEEDED, INCLUDING TRANSMISSION
27 LINES AND SUBSTATIONS;

HOUSE BILL 1411 9
1 (VI) CONSIDERATIONS FOR DEVELOPMENT RESTRICTIONS,
2 INCLUDING SIZE LIMITATIONS; AND
3 (VII) CONSIDERATIONS FOR COUNTY GRANTS, LOANS, AND TAX
4 CREDITS.
5 (E) IN DEVELOPING THE PLAN, THE LOCAL JURISDICTION SHALL HOLD AT
6 LEAST TWO MEETINGS TO SOLICIT PUBLIC INPUT.
7 (F) A LOCAL JURISDICTION SHALL ADOPT:
8 (1) ZONING REGULATIONS TO IMPLEMENT THE PLAN, INCLUDING
9 REGULATIONS GOVERNING WHERE LARGE–SCALE DATA CENTERS WILL BE:
10 (I) PROHIBITED;
11 (II) ALLOWED BY SPECIAL EXCEPTION; AND
12 (III) ALLOWED BY RIGHT, IF APPLICABLE;
13 (2) ANY ZONING OVERLAYS DEEMED NECESSARY TO IMPLEMENT THE
14 PLAN; AND
15 (3) ANY OTHER ZONING REQUIREMENT OR RESTRICTION DEEMED
16 NECESSARY TO IMPLEMENT THE PLAN.
17 (G) THE DEPARTMENT OF PLANNING:
18 (1) SHALL PUBLISH EACH LARGE–SCALE DATA CENTER PLAN WITHIN
19 30 DAYS AFTER RECEIVING THE PLAN FROM A LOCAL JURISDICTION; AND
20 (2) MAY DEVELOP GUIDANCE, MODEL ORDINANCES, AND OTHER
21 RESOURCES TO ASSIST LOCAL JURISDICTIONS IN PLANNING FOR DATA CENTER
22 DEVELOPMENT.
23 Article – State Finance and Procurement
24 7–240.
25 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
26 INDICATED.

10 HOUSE BILL 1411
1 (2) “DATA CENTER” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN § 11–239 OF THE
2 TAX – GENERAL ARTICLE.
3 (3) “LARGE–SCALE DATA CENTER” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN §
4 4–217 OF THE LAND USE ARTICLE.
5 (B) AN OFFICER OR A UNIT OF STATE GOVERNMENT MAY NOT USE ANY PART
6 OF AN APPROPRIATION TO PROVIDE A GRANT, LOAN, OR OTHER FINANCIAL
7 ASSISTANCE OR INCENTIVE TO AN OWNER OR OPERATOR OF A LARGE–SCALE DATA
8 CENTER UNLESS:
9 (1) THE OWNER OR OPERATOR IS IN COMPLIANCE WITH § 19–102 OF
10 THE ENVIRONMENT ARTICLE; AND
11 (2) THE LOCAL JURISDICTION IN WHICH THE LARGE–SCALE DATA
12 CENTER WILL BE LOCATED HAS ADOPTED A LARGE–SCALE DATA CENTER PLAN AND
13 THE ZONING REGULATIONS NECESSARY TO IMPLEMENT THE PLAN, IN ACCORDANCE
14 WITH § 4–217 OF THE LAND USE ARTICLE.
15 Article – Tax – General
16 11–239.
17 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
18 (2) “Data center” means a building or group of buildings used to house
19 computer systems, computer storage equipment, and associated infrastructure that
20 businesses or other organizations use to organize, process, store, and disseminate large
21 amounts of data.
22 (3) “Department” means the Department of Commerce.
23 (c) (1) To qualify for the sales and use tax exemption under subsection (b) of
24 this section, an individual or a corporation shall file an application for an exemption
25 certificate with the Department.
26 (2) (I) The application must:
27 [(i)] 1. demonstrate that the applicant intends to meet the
28 requirements of a qualified data center; and
29 [(ii)] 2. include any information the Department requires to
30 evidence the capacity and intention of the applicant to fulfill the commitments set forth in
31 the applicant’s application.

HOUSE BILL 1411 11
1 (II) IN ADDITION TO THE REQUIREMENTS UNDER
2 SUBPARAGRAPH (I) OF THIS PARAGRAPH, FOR A LARGE–SCALE DATA CENTER, AS
3 DEFINED IN § 4–217 OF THE LAND USE ARTICLE, THE APPLICATION MUST
4 DEMONSTRATE THAT:
5 1. THE APPLICANT IS IN COMPLIANCE WITH § 19–102 OF
6 THE ENVIRONMENT ARTICLE; AND
7 2. THE LOCAL JURISDICTION IN WHICH THE
8 LARGE–SCALE DATA CENTER IS LOCATED HAS ADOPTED A LARGE–SCALE DATA
9 CENTER PLAN AND THE ZONING REGULATIONS NECESSARY TO IMPLEMENT THE
10 PLAN, IN ACCORDANCE WITH § 4–217 OF THE LAND USE ARTICLE.
11 (3) If, based on the information and supporting documentation provided in
12 the application, the Department determines the applicant is eligible for the sales and use
13 tax exemption under subsection (b) of this section, the Department shall certify the
14 eligibility of the applicant.
15 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
16 1, 2026.

